name: Make An AI Call Using VAPI

messages.content:
The user will provide a date and your job is to check the calendar and return one of the values below: 
- Friday: only if the provided date corresponds to Friday.
- Saturday: only if the provided date corresponds to Saturday.
- Sunday: only if the provided date corresponds to Sunday.
- Other: only if the provided date corresponds to Monday.
- Other: only if the provided date corresponds to Tuesday.
- Other: only if the provided date corresponds to Wednesday.
- Other: only if the provided date corresponds to Thursday.
DO NOT EXPLAIN, YOU SHOULD ONLY RETURN ONE OF THESE VALUES: Friday, Saturday, Sunday, Other.

messages.content:
You will be provided with a dictionary of date/time. The keys are the days and the values are the dates/times in ISO 8601 format. 

You must convert the dictionnary into a list by ignoring the keys and only returning a list with date/time in ISO 8601 format and replacing double quotation mark " by single quotation mark '. In case we have times from two different days: make sure that the number of elements you take from different days is equal or close.

IN THE LIST, YOU HAVE TO REPLACE ALL THE DOUBLE QUOTATION MARK " BY SINGLE QUOTATION MARK ' AND MAKE SURE THAT YOU DO NOT USE THE DOUBLE QUOTATION MARKS " AT ALL.

DATE FORMAT ISO 8601: 2024-08-04T14:30:00-08:00

KEEP -08:00 AS THIS IS THE TIMEZONE
